Cholangiocarcinoma of the main biliary tract. Judging its resectability by imaging procedures. Eighteen patients with main biliary tract cholangiocarcinomas and no spread to the gallbladder and to the papilla of Vater underwent a combined US, ERCP/PTC and CT study. Angiography was performed on a selected group of 12 patients. We divided the infiltrating, polypoid or stenosing lesions in three groups: upper portion tumors, involving the confluence and the common hepatic duct (8 patients) middle portion tumors, originating from the common bile duct between the confluence of the cystic duct and the upper duodenal profile (6 patients)